# Shell scripts must use LF so bash on Windows (git-bash, WSL) can execute them.
# Without this, git core.autocrlf=true rewrites .sh files with CRLF on checkout,
# producing `$'\r': command not found` errors when bash interprets the script.
# Other text files (.lua, .menu, .tp2, .py) are left alone — Lua, WeiDU, and
# Python all tolerate CRLF, and forcing normalization here would churn the diff.
*.sh text eol=lf
